Implement the following plan:

# Add view tracking to ExplorePage

## Context
When clicking posts in `ExplorePage.jsx` (hottest posts, runner-up cards, search results, suggestions), views are not tracked. `PostCards.jsx` already tracks views via `useAddViewsMutation` before navigating. This change makes ExplorePage consistent.

## Changes

### `client/src/components/HomePage/explore/ExplorePage.jsx`

1. **Add import** (after line 12):
   ```js
   import { useAddViewsMutation } from "../../../utils/useMutation";
   ```

2. **Create mutateViews instance** (inside `ExplorePage` component, after line 186 near `userId`):
   ```js
   const mutateViews = useAddViewsMutation(session);
   ```

3. **Add view tracking to `handleClickPost`** (line 287-296) — fire mutation before navigating:
   ```js
   const handleClickPost = (journalId) => {
       if(!journalId) return;
       if(!session){
           openAuthModal();
           return;
       }
       const formadata = new FormData();
       formadata.append('journalId', journalId);
       mutateViews.mutate(formadata);
       navigate(`/home/post/${journalId}`);
   };
   ```

4. **Add view tracking to `handleClickSuggestion`** (line 271-285) — fire mutation before navigating:
   ```js
   const handleClickSuggestion = (journal) => {
       if(!journal?.id) return;
       if(!session){
           openAuthModal();
           return;
       }
       setIsSearchFocused(false);
       if(journal?.title){
           setSearchInput(journal.title);
           setDebouncedSearchInput(journal.title);
       }
       const formadata = new FormData();
       formadata.append('journalId', journal.id);
       mutateViews.mutate(formadata);
       navigate(`/home/post/${journal.id}`);
   };
   ```

## Verification
- Click a hero card, runner-up card, and search result on the Explore page
- Click a suggestion from the search dropdown
- Confirm `addViews` API calls fire in the network tab for each
- Confirm navigation still works correctly


